Police are searching for four armed men who robbed the McDonald s outlet in Linton Grange on Saturday morning. Police spokeswoman Colonel Priscilla Naidu said the fast food joint was robbed at 3.17am. Four armed men entered the building and held up the cashier. They took an undisclosed amount of cash, she said. The men got in through an open window. Naidu said the suspects fired shots at security guards who arrived at the scene during the robbery. However, the robbers managed to flee. Share on Facebook Share Share on Twitter Tweet Share on Google Plus Share